,"marks":1,"options":["Finger flexion","Forearm pronation","Elbow extension","Wrist flexion","Finger adduction"],"correctOptions":[4],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe C7 myotome is primarily responsible for movements such as \u003Cstrong\u003Eelbow extension\u003C/strong\u003E, \u003Cstrong\u003Ewrist flexion\u003C/strong\u003E, and finger extension. \u003Cstrong\u003EFinger adduction\u003C/strong\u003E is primarily controlled by the T1 myotome, not C7.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EFinger flexion\u003C/strong\u003E - Involves C7 as well as C8\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EForearm pronation\u003C/strong\u003E - Involves C7 as well as C6\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EElbow extension\u003C/strong\u003E - Primarily involves C7\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EWrist flexion\u003C/strong\u003E - Involves C7 as well as C6\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EUnderstanding the distribution of myotomes is important for diagnosing nerve root injuries and their impact on muscle function.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["The C7 myotome is primarily responsible for elbow extension, wrist flexion, and finger extension.","Finger adduction is primarily controlled by the T1 myotome.","Understanding myotomes is crucial for diagnosing nerve root injuries."],"references":["Sonoo M. Recent advances in neuroanatomy: the myotome update. J Neurol Neurosurg Psychiatry. 2023 Aug;94(8):643-648. doi: 10.1136/jnnp-2022-329696. Epub 2023 Jan 18. PMID: 36653172","Kaiser JT, Lugo-Pico JG. Neuroanatomy, Spinal Nerves. [Updated 2023 Aug 14]. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan-. Available from: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK542218/","Singh, V. (2024). Textbook of Clinical Neuroanatomy-E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences","Michael-Titus, A. T., \u0026 Shortland, P. (2022). The Nervous System, E-Book: The Nervous System, E-Book. Elsevier Health Science","Howard, R., Kullmann, D., Werring, D., \u0026 Zandi, M. (Eds.). (2024). Neurology: a queen square textbook. John Wiley \u0026 Sons"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"55159"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17284"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"55159","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/55159"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-12T14:40:58+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-12T14:42:01+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"9974"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"69706"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/74"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Level I","synonyms":null,"description":"Remember (identifying and retrieving information)","position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"7"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"3000","links":{"self":"https://app.eme